# most important
- improve special function precision


# publication-grade gaps (auditable → publication-grade)
## filed as issues
- #211  erf/erfc: replace series expansion with continued fraction for tail accuracy
- #212  property tests: PDF non-negativity, CDF monotonicity, quantile roundtrip
- #213  quantile() reference values via scipy ppf() for 12 core continuous distributions
- #214  catastrophic cancellation audit and fix (1 - exp(...) patterns near boundaries)
- #135  second parameter set per distribution + refVals for each new set

## not yet filed
- far-tail refVals for Normal/LogNormal (±5σ, ±7σ) to expose and track erf accuracy
- complete refVals series for all ~120 distributions (only 12 continuous covered so far)
- refVals and property tests for discrete distributions (Binomial, Poisson, NegativeBinomial, …)
- validate special functions (gammaLowerIncomplete, betaIncomplete, Bessel, digamma, …)
  across full input domains against scipy/boost, not just spot checks
- systematic parameter-space coverage: grid of parameter values per distribution,
  not just two hand-picked sets
- document accuracy bounds: "Normal CDF accurate to X ULP for |x| ≤ Y" etc.


